<blockquote>"Q: Can you explain how the overlapping Focus items will stack, particularly with mana reduction items?<br>
<br>
A:When casting a spell, <b>you get the benefit of the best focus item of a given type</b>. If you cast a DoT spell and were wearing a Mana Preservation item (-10% mana cost) and an Affliction Efficency item (-25% mana cost), you would use the Affliction Efficiency item bonus.<br>
<br>
If you had on the same gear and you cast a direct damage spell, it would use the Mana Preservation item bonus instead, since Affliction Efficiency only works with DoTs. <br>
<br>
Focus effects of different types will work together however. If you have on a mana saving item, a spell haste item, and a duration extending item, all three of these can work on the same spell. <b>It's only items of the same focus type that don't stack.</b> <br>
<br>
- Rich"</blockquote> <br>
<br>
<br>
<i>1) Does Extended Enhancement stack with our AA ability, or is that rumoured max of 50% on buff length enhancement true?</i><br>
<br>
I don't have one of those items, so I can't answer this one.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>2) Extended Enhancement works on Regeneration spells I believe, but does it work on clickable buffs and Group buffs? (I believe our AA ability works on group buffs but not clickable buffs, not positive though).</i><br>
<br>
On the Shaman's Crucible some <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?s=&threadid=2340">said</a> it didn't work on group buffs. Perhaps that was fixed in the last patch. Can anyone else confirm? I have a Mana Preservation III item and it worked when I cast POTG yesterday, so I don't know why the other focus item wouldn't, but then again, consistency isn't always consistently applied. =\ On the other hand, Alan said this about the duration: "Spell duration foci affecting beneficial spells are no longer random. They now always extend the affected buffs for their maximum. (We never wanted to make it harder to time your buffs.)" <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
</i>3) Will Affliction efficiency stack with SCM or Mana Conservation to give a >25% mana reduction?</i><br>
<br>
The higher one wins out (Affliction Efficiency over Mana Preservation). No stacking there.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>4) Does Extended Affliction work on right click dot's? I have Affliction Haste and I know the haste does not affect my Velious bracer or epic casting time :-(, but dont have extended affliction to test it.</i><br>
<br>
Yes, if the dot is a normal spell from your spellbook like Drones of Doom. I have used my Coldain Military Wristguard with my Velious bracer. <br>
<br>
<i>5) Anyone know the max on Extended Affliction? is it 50% or 100%?</i><br>
<br>
20%<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>6) is Extended affliction a random 1 - 20% increase in the DoT time or a static 20% increase for all casts? I believe the mana conservation and affliction efficiency are random so I was not sure about this one.</i><br>
<br>
Seems variable just like Improved Healing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>7) Is there a max to extended range. 45% 60% 75%?</i><br>
<br>
Max was supposed to be 15%, but some players <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=17356.topic">posted on Graffe's</a> this was slightly bugged due to the z-axis being used now in determing casting range. Others reported it's working fine.<br>
<br>
<br>
