<br>
Thanks for the answers so far, I totally missed the post on Casters Realm.<br>
<br>
I will assume for now that the Extended Enhancement not working on group buffs is a mess-up on VI's part.<br>
<br>
If what I know now is correct we should be able to stack 50% AA ability and 20% from Extended Enhancement (I think it was 20% for that focus affect) to get a total of 70% extension to our buff times.  This would affectively make NR 5 mins and 6 seconds long or a total of 1530hps healed over that time.<br>
<br>
I will log back in soon and re-test the Affliction Haste and see if it now works on right click dot's (dod bracer).  If the Extended Affliction works with the bracer then it is only logical that the Affliction Haste should as well.  30% less cast time on that bracer would allow me to use it a bit more just to add a bit more damage but not make me stand still casting for a whole 7 seconds in a fight where every second counts.<br>
<br>
I was also taking a look at the damage/mana ratio's of Drifting Death and Winged Death.  I just got home from work and I am too lazy to go cut and paste the numbers right now, but DD is *very* close to WD in mana/damage ratio (they both have the same timing relatively).  Because DD is level 44 and as we know focus II will work on level 44 spells.  SO if you take Coldain military wrist guard (Extended Affliction III) and Grey Flesh Gloves (Affliction Efficiency II) you can make that level 44 DoT very inexpensive to cast and it will last a while and do some significant damage.  More efficient then WD by far and tied or very close the BoR.  Of course if you are able to get an item with Affliction Efficiency III on it then WD would be the way to go, but for us non-NToV(and such armours) equiped types we most likely wont be able to.<br>
<br>
